<!DOCTYPE score-partwise PUBLIC "-//Recordare//DTD MusicXML 3.0 Partwise//EN" "http://www.musicxml.org/dtds/partwise.dtd">
<score-partwise>
  <work>
    <work-number>(also known as Jesus We Now Must Laud and Sing or From East to West)</work-number>
    <work-title>Now Praise We Christ, the Holy One</work-title>
  </work>
  <identification>
    <creator type="composer">Words: Coelius Sedulius, circa 450.  Translated to German by Martin Luther, 1524.
Translated from German to English by Richard Massie, 1854, alt.
Music: 'Christum Wir Sollen Loben Schon' ancient Latin found in Erfurt Enchiridion, 1524.
Setting: Michael Praetorius, 1609.
copyright: public domain.  This score is a part of the Open Hymnal Project, 2009 Revision.</creator>
    <encoding>
      <encoder>abc2xml version 268</encoder>
      <software>https://wim.vree.org/svgParse/abc2xml.html</software>
      <encoding-date>2026-07-21</encoding-date>
    </encoding>
    <miscellaneous>
      <miscellaneous-field name="lyrics">6. In a rude manger, stretched on hay, In poverty content He lay;
With milk was fed the Lord of all, Who feeds the ravens when they call.

7. Th' angelic choir rejoice, and raise Their voice to God in songs of praise;
To humble shepherds is proclaimed The Shepherd who the world hath framed.

8. Honor to Thee, O Christ, be paid, Pure offspring of a holy maid,
With Father and with Holy Ghost, Till time in time's abyss be lost.</miscellaneous-field>
    </miscellaneous>
  </identification>
